                <p class="work-heading">Nadan Kozhi Varuthathu (Spicy Chicken Fry)</p>
                <p class="work-text">Want to add spice on your palate? Then, you must try one of the national foods of Kerala that is
                    spicy chicken fry or Kerala style prawn curry as there is no single national food of Kerala. 
                    Served with onion, spices, garlic, and vinegar on a banana leaf, Nadan Kozhi Varuthathu is fried chicken
                    made with a generous amount of spices.
                    One can have it with chapattis, Kerala Porotta (a layered flatbread made from maida flour), appam or rice. 
                    It also serves as a popular street food in the list of Kerala dishes served with dosa. 
